Hi Beth,

When you have an odd number of values, the median is the one in the
middle.  With an even number of values, the median is the mean of the
two values in the middle.  So the median of 

  0, 2, 3, 4, 4, 5

would be (3+4)/2, or 3.5.  

Does this help?

